                            <comment id="15206411" author="beobal" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 14:06:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch introduces some regressions as Clustering serialization assumes the clustering always contains a value (possibly null) for every clustering column, and the changes here make that assumption invalid. I&apos;ll update with a new patch presently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15206988" author="beobal" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 18:34:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stupidly I&apos;d made the queries produce invalid &lt;tt&gt;ClusteringIndexNamesFilter&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;ClusteringIndexSliceFilter&lt;/tt&gt;. Fixed and pushed, CI is running now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15208987" author="jrwest" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2016 19:21:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=beobal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;beobal&quot;&gt;beobal&lt;/a&gt; the patch looks good and i&apos;ve confirmed your fix locally. One small piece of feedback: since you fixed things to return a &lt;tt&gt;ClusteringIndexSliceFilter&lt;/tt&gt; I don&apos;t think the &lt;tt&gt;isLike&lt;/tt&gt; check in &lt;tt&gt;PrimaryKeyRestrictionSet#appendTo&lt;/tt&gt; is necessary anymore (i&apos;ve removed it locally without issue). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15210102" author="beobal" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2016 11:30:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, I&apos;ve committed to 3.5 (with the unnecessary isLike check removed) in &lt;tt&gt;3fda52f247415c1eace35af80c74bc433a57254b&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
